*{{audio|en-us-like.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|like|likes|liked|liking}}
#''(transitive)'' To [[enjoy]], be in favor/favour of.
#:''I '''like''' hamburgers.''
#:''I '''like''' the Milwaukee Braves this season.''
#''(transitive)'' To [[find]] [[attractive]].
#:''I really '''like''' Sandra but don't know how to tell her.''

====Synonyms====
*(''enjoy''): [[appreciate]], [[enjoy]]
*(''find attractive''): be [[attract]]ed to, [[fancy]] (''British'')

====Antonyms====
*(''enjoy''): [[dislike]], [[hate]]

