===Particle===
'''like'''

#(''slang, somewhat dated'') A [[mild]] [[w:intensifier|intensifier]].
#:'''''Like''', why did you do that?''
#(''slang'') When preceded by any form of the verb '''to be''', used to mean "to say".
#:''I was '''like''', "Why did you do that?" and he's '''like''', "I don't know."''

====Usage notes====
#The sense meaning "to say" is deliberately informal and commonly used by young people, and often combined with the use of the present tense as a narrative.  Similar terms are ''to go'' and ''all'', as in ''I go, "Why did you do that?" and he goes, "I don't know"'' and ''I was all, "Why did you do that?" and he was all, "I don't know."''  The forms with ''like'' and ''all'' can imply that the attributed remark which follows is representative rather than necessarily an exact quotation.

====Synonyms====
*(''say''): be [[all]], [[go]]

